text: Billy Bainbridge (born 9 September 1997) is an Australian professional rugby league footballer who plays as a and for the Manly Warringah Sea Eagles in the National Rugby League. ==Background== Bainbridge was born in Cromer, New South Wales, Australia. He played his junior rugby league for the Manly Christian Brothers, before being signed by the Manly Warringah Sea Eagles. ==Playing career== ===2015=== In 2015 and 2016, Bainbridge played for the Manly Warringah Sea Eagles' NYC team. In August 2015, he re-signed with the Sea Eagles on a 2-year contract until the end of 2017. ===2016=== In round 26 of the 2016 NRL season, Bainbridge made his NRL debut for the Sea Eagles against the Penrith Panthers. ==References== ==External links== *Manly Warringah Sea Eagles profile Category:1997 births Category:Australian rugby league players Category:Manly Warringah Sea Eagles players Category:Rugby league second-rows Category:Rugby league locks Category:Living people Category:Rugby league players from Sydney
